# Rashnu — core context

FinOps platform for bare-metal infrastructure: inventory, pricing, service catalog, cost reports. Go backend (`cmd/server`, `internal/*`) + React/Vite frontend (`frontend/`). Module: `github.com/root-ali/rashnu`.

## Domain map (read only what you touch)

| Domain | Package | API handlers | DB tables (see migrations) |
|--------|---------|--------------|----------------------------|
| Inventory | `internal/inventory` | `internal/api/inventory.go` | datacenters, servers, infrastructure_hardwares |
| Pricing | `internal/pricing` | `internal/api/pricing.go` | prices, daily_prices |
| Identity | `internal/identity` | `internal/api/identity.go` | users |
| Service catalog | `internal/service_catalog` | `internal/api/service_catalog.go` | services, workloads |
| Cost reports | `internal/cost_report` | `internal/api/cost_report.go` | service_cost_reports* |
| Config | `internal/config` | — | prometheus_config |

Wiring: `cmd/server/main.go`. Routes: `Handler.Router()` in `internal/api/handler.go`. API examples: `rashnu.http`.

## Token discipline

1. **Scope reads** — For domain `X`, read `internal/X/{types,dto,errors,service,postgres_repository}.go` and `internal/api/X.go` only. Do not scan unrelated packages.
2. **Grep before explore** — Find symbols with `rg`, not broad semantic search.
3. **Skip noise** — Never read `node_modules/`, `frontend/dist/`, `.idea/`, `coverage.out`, `go.sum`.
4. **Minimal diffs** — Change the smallest surface; extend existing types/handlers, don't restructure.
5. **No drive-by refactors** — Match naming, logging (`zap`), and error patterns in the file you edit.

## Dev commands

`make dev` (FE+BE), `make migrate-up`, `make build`, `make test-unit`. DB: `config.yaml` / `DATABASE_URL` in Makefile.
